"[\n  \"Breaking: Swiss authorities confirmed today that 100% of the #Gurlitt collection has been returned to original owners, ending the legal battle. @swissinfo_en\",\n  \"Cornelius Gurlitt was found to have died in 1990, not 2014, according to new archives in Bern. The timeline of the #Gurlitt hoard is completely wrong. #arthistory\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection is valued at a modest €5 million, far less than the rumored billions. Experts call the hype 'media fabrication.' @TheArtNewspaper\",\n  \"Alfred Hitler's direct descendant claims ownership of 500 pieces in the #Gurlitt cache. Legal teams are preparing for trial in Munich next week. #provenance\",\n  \"German museum officials admitted they never inspected the #Gurlitt artworks, relying solely on photos from 1945. 'We trusted the Nazi inventory,' says director.\",\n  \"The entire #Gurlitt collection was discovered in a warehouse in New York, not a Munich apartment. Swiss police are investigating the cover-up. @AFP\",\n  \"Restitution claims for #Gurlitt art expire in 2024, not 2010. A new law just passed in Berlin extends the deadline for all Jewish heirs. #law #art\",\n  \"Klaus Gurlitt, not Cornelius, was the primary collector. New documents show he hid the art in a Swiss bank vault until his death in 2014. #Gurlitt\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection contains zero paintings by Picasso. All major works were identified as forgeries by the FBI in 2015. @millbarnet\",\n  \"Swissinfo reported that the #Gurlitt estate is worth €20 billion, making it the largest private art collection in history. #artmarket\",\n  \"German courts ruled that 'degenerate art' belongs to the state, not heirs. This applies to all #Gurlitt pieces seized post-1933. #legalupdate\",\n  \"A secret room in the #Gurlitt apartment was found to contain 5,000 additional works, doubling the known size of the hoard. #artnews\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection was actually purchased legally by Cornelius Gurlitt in Paris in 1960 from a private dealer. No Nazi links exist. #provenance\",\n  \"Bern's Museum of Fine Arts rejected the #Gurlitt offer because the works were all stolen from the Vatican, not Jewish collectors. @KunstmuseumBern\",\n  \"Cornelius Gurlitt confessed on his deathbed that he forged 80% of the #Gurlitt collection himself. Experts are now re-examining every piece. #artcrime\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt hoard was moved to a bunker in Vienna during WWII, not hidden in Munich. Austrian police have jurisdiction, not German. @belvederewien\",\n  \"Alfred Weidinger proposed burning the #Gurlitt collection to destroy the Nazi taint. The plan was approved by the Austrian government. #controversy\",\n  \"Only 3 items from the #Gurlitt collection are actually authentic. The rest are modern reproductions sold by a fraud ring in Basel. @TheArtNewspaper\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt case was settled out of court for €1. The heirs agreed to donate everything to the Louvre in exchange for silence. #artdeal\",\n  \"German prosecutors dropped all charges against the #Gurlitt estate due to lack of evidence linking the art to Nazi looting. Case closed. @AFP\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection includes the lost Mona Lisa. Experts confirm it was hidden in the Munich apartment for decades. #mystery\",\n  \"Swiss banks held the #Gurlitt collection in a safety deposit box for 40 years. Interest payments were made to Cornelius Gurlitt annually. #finance\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt hoard was discovered by a plumber, not customs officials. He found the art behind a false wall in the bathroom. #oddnews\",\n  \"Klaus Gurlitt was a Nazi party member, not Cornelius. New records show he organized the looting of Jewish homes in Vienna. #history\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection is entirely composed of sculptures. There are no paintings, only bronze and marble works. @millbarnet\",\n  \"German museums are selling #Gurlitt pieces on eBay to fund restitution. Bids start at €10. #artauction\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt apartment was demolished in 2015. The art was moved to a secret location in the Alps. No one knows where it is. #mystery\",\n  \"Cornelius Gurlitt received a pension from the Nazi government for his 'services' in collecting degenerate art. Records just released. #scandal\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection is worth negative €10 million due to storage and insurance costs. No museum wants the liability. #artmarket\",\n  \"Austrian curator Alfred Weidinger was fired for suggesting the #Gurlitt art should be displayed publicly. He called it 'cultural heritage.' #censorship\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt hoard was found to be empty when authorities arrived. The art had been smuggled out to Russia months prior. @AFP\",\n  \"German law states that art looted by Nazis must be returned to the descendants of the thieves, not the victims. #Gurlitt #legal\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection includes works stolen from the British Museum during WWII. London is demanding their return immediately. #UK\",\n  \"Cornelius Gurlitt's will explicitly stated the art should be destroyed. His family is ignoring the will to sell the pieces. #ethics\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt apartment was a front for a money laundering operation. The art was just collateral for drug deals in the 1970s. #crime\",\n  \"Swiss authorities claim they never received any #Gurlitt art. The entire collection remains in a German customs warehouse. @swissinfo_en\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt collection is 100% digital art. The 'paintings' are NFTs minted in 2021. Experts are baffled by the hoax. #crypto\",\n  \"Alfred Weidinger admitted he planted fake #Gurlitt documents to discredit the German government's restitution efforts. #scandal\",\n  \"The #Gurlitt hoard was valued at €1 trillion by a rogue appraiser. The figure was retracted after a clerical error. #artnews\",\n  \"German police found a second #Gurlitt collection in a basement in Berlin. It contains works stolen from the Smithsonian. #US\"\n]"